      "description": "Available is a mechanically sorted 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six. This power unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system to deliver a linear power band up to an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and sent to the rear wheels through a variable M-differential lock. Significant preventative maintenance has been addressed, including rear subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive VANOS bulletproofing. The chassis retains its factory-spec MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry, offering precise turn-in and communicative feedback. While the aesthetic condition reflects its status as a driven enthusiast car, the drivetrain and structural integrity remain robust, making it an ideal candidate for spirited canyon carving or track-day duty.",
